<p>I maintain and contribute to several awesome-* lists on GitHub. â€œAwesomeâ€ lists, started by <em><a href="https://github.com/sindresorhus">Sindre Sorhus</a></em>, are collaboratively built lists of things that are, well, awesome. They have helped change how the GitHub community curates its ecosystem, allowing for easier entry and recall of important links.</p>

<p>On GitHub, users can â€˜starâ€™ repositories to show that they like them and to bookmark them for later use. The stars below are a good metric for user engagement with these lists.</p>

